* Cracking ZIP and RAR passwords with John the Ripper involves a two-step process:
* 1. Extracting the password hash from the archive
* 2. Using JtR to crack that hash

* 1. Extract the Archive Hash
John the Ripper cannot work directly on archive files; it requires a text-based hash representation.
You must use the appropriate utility script to generate this hash.
I have created a zip file called sample.zip with a password and I am going to Crack it.
We will use the command: 'zip2john <zip file name>.zip' and the hash will be output
I then will extract it to a .txt file:
I will use the command 'zip2john <zip file name>.zip > hash.txt'
